---
title: Alert Banners
description: Info, success, warning, and error alert variants styled with CSS custom properties.
slug: alert-banner
cssFile: alert-banner.css
explanation: "Alert variants share a base `.alert` class and extend it with modifier classes like `.alert-success`. Each modifier applies a `background` using color palette variables like `var(--teal-dim)` and a `border-left` in the matching accent color, creating a consistent visual system. The dismissible variant uses a hidden checkbox — checking it sets `display: none` on the alert via the `~` sibling combinator."
---
{% extends "example.njk" %}
{% block demo %}
<div class="alerts">
	<div class="alert alert-info">
		<span class="alert-icon">ℹ</span>
		<div class="alert-body">
			<strong>Info</strong>
			Your password will expire in 7 days.
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="alert alert-success">
		<span class="alert-icon">✓</span>
		<div class="alert-body">
			<strong>Success</strong>
			Your profile was updated successfully.
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="alert alert-warning">
		<span class="alert-icon">⚠</span>
		<div class="alert-body">
			<strong>Warning</strong>
			You have unsaved changes on this page.
		</div>
	</div>
	<input type="checkbox" id="dismiss-1" class="alert-dismiss-input">
	<div class="alert alert-error alert-dismissible">
		<span class="alert-icon">✕</span>
		<div class="alert-body">
			<strong>Error</strong>
			Failed to connect. Check your network.
		</div>
		<label for="dismiss-1" class="alert-close">✕</label>
	</div>
</div>
{% endblock %}

{% block html_code %}
{%- highlight "html" %}
<div class="alert alert-success">
  <span class="alert-icon">✓</span>
  <div class="alert-body">
    <strong>Success</strong>
    Your changes were saved.
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Dismissible -->
<input type="checkbox" id="close-alert" class="alert-dismiss-input">
<div class="alert alert-error alert-dismissible">
  <strong>Error</strong> Something went wrong.
  <label for="close-alert" class="alert-close">✕</label>
</div>
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}

{% block css_code %}
{%- highlight "css" %}
.alert-success {
  background: rgba(87,217,163,.1);
  border-left: 3px solid var(--teal);
  color: var(--teal);
}

/* Dismissible pattern */
.alert-dismiss-input { display: none; }
.alert-dismiss-input:checked ~ .alert-dismissible {
  display: none;
}
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}
